Package com.jnape.palatable.lambda.traversable

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Traversable<A,T extends Traversable>
    An interface for a class of data structures that can be "traversed from left to right" in a structure-preserving way, successively applying some applicative computation to each element and collapsing the results into a single resulting applicative.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    TraversableIterable<A>
    Wrap an Iterable in a Traversable such that Traversable.traverse(Function, Function) applies its computation against each element of the wrapped Iterable.
    TraversableOptional<A>
    Wrap an Optional in a Traversable such that Traversable.traverse(Function, Function) applies its computation against the value wrapped by the wrapped Optional (if the Optional is present).
    Traversables
    Static factory methods for adapting core JDK types to Traversable.
    TraversablesTest
